00:01:24.430 --> 00:01:28.870
The famous result for the
Einstein A coefficient,

00:01:28.870 --> 00:01:30.895
which is also the
natural aligned width

00:01:30.895 --> 00:01:36.895
of the atomic excited state.

00:01:36.895 --> 00:01:41.250
Do you have any questions
about the derivation

00:01:41.250 --> 00:01:42.760
or what we did last week?

00:01:49.870 --> 00:01:53.435
Then I think I will just
continue and interpret

00:01:53.435 --> 00:01:55.100
the result.

00:01:55.100 --> 00:01:57.520
So we go to result for an
Einstein A coefficient.

00:01:57.520 --> 00:02:00.690
And well, the question
is, how big is it?

00:02:00.690 --> 00:02:08.830
Well it has a
number of constants.

00:02:08.830 --> 00:02:16.930
And if it is-- let's discuss
it now in atomic units.

00:02:16.930 --> 00:02:20.990
Well, if we assume the
frequency or the energy

00:02:20.990 --> 00:02:23.260
is on the order of
Rydberg-- that's

00:02:23.260 --> 00:02:26.330
sort of the measure for
an electronic excitation

00:02:26.330 --> 00:02:32.070
in the atom-- we assume the
dipole matrix element is one.

00:02:32.070 --> 00:02:35.530
That means one per radius.

00:02:35.530 --> 00:02:38.330
Since we have pretty much set
everything one and expressed

00:02:38.330 --> 00:02:42.580
everything in atomic units, it
means that the speed of light

00:02:42.580 --> 00:02:45.600
is-- remember?

00:02:45.600 --> 00:02:50.040
The velocity of the atom
in any correspondent

00:02:50.040 --> 00:02:53.110
was alpha times smaller
than the speed of light.

00:02:53.110 --> 00:02:56.190
But the velocity of the
atom is one atomic unit.

00:02:56.190 --> 00:02:59.370
So therefore, the speed
of light in atomic units

00:02:59.370 --> 00:03:02.070
is one over alpha.

00:03:02.070 --> 00:03:05.290
And that means that if
you look at the formula,

00:03:05.290 --> 00:03:08.110
there is the speed of
light to the power of 3

00:03:08.110 --> 00:03:09.740
in the denominator.

00:03:09.740 --> 00:03:13.120
And that means that
in atomic units

00:03:13.120 --> 00:03:15.920
the Einstein A
coefficient is alpha

00:03:15.920 --> 00:03:22.370
to the 3, which is 3
times 10 to the minus 7.

00:03:26.260 --> 00:03:31.600
So that means that the ratio
of this spontaneous emission

00:03:31.600 --> 00:03:34.610
rate, which is also
the inverse lifetime

00:03:34.610 --> 00:03:36.867
and, therefore, the natural
alignments of the excited

00:03:36.867 --> 00:03:37.366
state.

00:03:42.930 --> 00:03:47.880
Relative to the transition
frequency, so the damping

00:03:47.880 --> 00:03:49.970
of the harmonic oscillator
or the two level

00:03:49.970 --> 00:03:55.340
system relative to the NFC
spacing of the oscillator.

00:03:55.340 --> 00:03:56.260
It's small.

00:03:56.260 --> 00:03:59.770
It's actually alpha cube.

00:03:59.770 --> 00:04:04.850
So if you take this 3
times 10 to the minus 7

00:04:04.850 --> 00:04:07.790
and multiply it with the
atomic unit of frequency,

00:04:07.790 --> 00:04:08.690
which is 2 Rydbergs.

00:04:08.690 --> 00:04:12.180
We obtain on the
order of 10 to 9.

00:04:16.680 --> 00:04:23.390
And it's a rate of 10
to the 9 per second.

00:04:23.390 --> 00:04:28.290
And that means that the lifetime
of a tubercle atomic level

00:04:28.290 --> 00:04:29.770
is on the order of 1 nanosecond.

00:04:32.350 --> 00:04:41.880
Well, often it's
10 200 nanosecond

00:04:41.880 --> 00:04:49.150
because many transition
frequencies are smaller

00:04:49.150 --> 00:04:52.870
by quite a factor than the
atomic unit of the transition

00:04:52.870 --> 00:04:54.000
frequency.

00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:57.950
Remember, the Rydberg frequency
would be deep in the UV.

00:04:57.950 --> 00:05:00.245
But a lot of atoms have
transitions in the visible.

00:05:13.030 --> 00:05:17.380
I highlighted already
when I derived it

00:05:17.380 --> 00:05:23.540
that the spontaneous emission
has this famous omega cube

00:05:23.540 --> 00:05:25.420
dependents.

00:05:25.420 --> 00:05:29.560
And that this actually
important to understand

00:05:29.560 --> 00:05:37.130
why lower lying levels--
excited hyperfine levels--

00:05:37.130 --> 00:05:39.470
do not radiate.

00:05:39.470 --> 00:05:43.250
So let me just, kind
of, formalize it.

00:05:43.250 --> 00:05:48.210
If I would now estimate what
is the radiative lifetime

00:05:48.210 --> 00:05:52.782
for a transition, which is not
as I just assumed in the UV

00:05:52.782 --> 00:05:53.680
or in the visible.

00:05:53.680 --> 00:05:57.370
Let me estimate what is the
radiative lifetime to emit

00:05:57.370 --> 00:05:59.300
a microwave photon
at a few gigahertz?

00:06:05.310 --> 00:06:14.410
Well, the microwave frequency
of the gigahertz 10 to the nine

00:06:14.410 --> 00:06:17.990
is five orders of magnitude
smaller than the frequency 10

00:06:17.990 --> 00:06:19.930
to the 14 of an
optical transition.

00:06:23.860 --> 00:06:29.640
So therefore, this is 10
to the 15 times longer.

00:06:29.640 --> 00:06:31.880
And if you have,
typically, one or ten

00:06:31.880 --> 00:06:34.400
nanosecond for an
electronic transition.

00:06:34.400 --> 00:06:38.360
That means that this spontaneous
lifetime for a microwave

00:06:38.360 --> 00:06:42.180
transition is seven months.

00:06:42.180 --> 00:06:50.250
If in addition we factor in
that hyperfine transitions have

00:06:50.250 --> 00:06:53.950
an operator which is a Bohr
magneton and magnetic type

00:06:53.950 --> 00:07:04.230
of operator, not an
electric dipole and we

00:07:04.230 --> 00:07:08.210
discussed that the Bohr
magneton is actually

00:07:08.210 --> 00:07:11.020
when we discuss multiple
transitions we discuss

00:07:11.020 --> 00:07:13.820
that the Bohr magneton
is alpha times smaller

00:07:13.820 --> 00:07:16.360
than a typical
electric dipole moment.

00:07:16.360 --> 00:07:19.840
So therefore, a magnetic
dipole transition

00:07:19.840 --> 00:07:27.160
is alpha times weaker than an
electronic dipole transition.

00:07:27.160 --> 00:07:30.880
And that means now, if
you multiply months, which

00:07:30.880 --> 00:07:33.100
we obtain by the
frequency scaling,

00:07:33.100 --> 00:07:35.400
again, by alpha square
for the weakness

00:07:35.400 --> 00:07:41.340
of the magnetic dipole, we find
that atomic hyperfine levels

00:07:41.340 --> 00:07:48.630
have a lifetime, which is
on the order of 1,000 years.

00:07:48.630 --> 00:07:51.034
And this is why it's
very safe to neglect

00:07:51.034 --> 00:07:52.450
those transition
in the laboratory

00:07:52.450 --> 00:07:56.970
and assume that all hyperfine
states in the ground state

00:07:56.970 --> 00:08:01.750
manifold pretty much don't
decay and are long lived.

00:08:07.476 --> 00:08:07.976
Questions?

00:08:14.940 --> 00:08:20.330
OK, so with that we have
discussed spontaneous emission.

00:08:24.444 --> 00:08:26.110
Let's go through a
few clicker questions

00:08:26.110 --> 00:08:39.630
to discuss the subject and
verify your understanding.

00:08:39.630 --> 00:08:56.540
So the first question
is can an E2 transition,

00:08:56.540 --> 00:09:07.920
which is a quadruple
transition, can you

00:09:07.920 --> 00:09:09.885
drive it by a plane wave?

00:09:12.930 --> 00:09:14.700
Or does it need a
laser beam which

00:09:14.700 --> 00:09:18.150
has an intensity gradient
such as a focus laser beam.

00:09:28.310 --> 00:09:29.240
Yes or no?

00:09:59.836 --> 00:10:00.335
OK.

00:10:03.260 --> 00:10:05.790
Well the answer is yes.

00:10:05.790 --> 00:10:08.330
You can just use
your laser beam.

00:10:08.330 --> 00:10:12.460
If a quadrupole transition
would require a gradient,

00:10:12.460 --> 00:10:14.550
it would really
require a gradient

00:10:14.550 --> 00:10:16.010
over the size of the atom.

00:10:16.010 --> 00:10:19.400
And that would be
extremely hard to achieve.

00:10:19.400 --> 00:10:22.860
Fortunately, this is not the
case because what happens

00:10:22.860 --> 00:10:25.980
is we actually assumed
in the derivation

00:10:25.980 --> 00:10:29.370
that we had a plane
wave into the IKR.

00:10:29.370 --> 00:10:32.680
And then do the
tailor expansion.

00:10:32.680 --> 00:10:35.920
And it was these part
of the tailor expansion

00:10:35.920 --> 00:10:39.950
of a plain wave, which gave
rise to the matrix element

00:10:39.950 --> 00:10:42.000
for the quadrupole transition.

00:10:42.000 --> 00:10:46.679
So a plane wave laser beam
is sufficient to drive

00:10:46.679 --> 00:10:47.845
higher multiple transitions.

00:10:50.590 --> 00:10:51.180
Next question.

00:10:55.880 --> 00:11:06.240
Can spontaneous
emission be described

00:11:06.240 --> 00:11:18.185
as a stimulated emission
process by the zero point field.

00:11:23.130 --> 00:11:26.539
So by the zero point field, we
know the electromagnetic wave

00:11:26.539 --> 00:11:27.580
is a harmonic oscillator.

00:11:27.580 --> 00:11:28.565
And a harmonic oscillator
has a ground state.

00:11:28.565 --> 00:11:31.270
And in the ground state
you have zero point motion.

00:11:31.270 --> 00:11:33.250
So there is an electric
field, even when

00:11:33.250 --> 00:11:34.830
we have the vacuum state.

00:11:34.830 --> 00:11:42.010
And the question is,
can spontaneous emission

00:11:42.010 --> 00:11:49.850
be described as simply being
stimulated emission but now do

00:11:49.850 --> 00:11:53.170
to the silver point fluctuations
of the electromagnetic field.

00:12:17.331 --> 00:12:17.830
OK.

00:12:20.670 --> 00:12:23.690
The answer is it depends.

00:12:23.690 --> 00:12:26.260
It depends if you just want to
make a qualitative hand waving

00:12:26.260 --> 00:12:26.760
argument.

00:12:29.260 --> 00:12:31.500
Then I would say
you are correct.

00:12:31.500 --> 00:12:35.090
You can say that the
electromagnetic field

00:12:35.090 --> 00:12:37.630
of the vacuum
stimulates a transition.

00:12:37.630 --> 00:12:42.340
But when I said
described, I meant

00:12:42.340 --> 00:12:45.290
if you can get it
quantitatively correct.

00:12:45.290 --> 00:12:48.090
And there the answer
is actually no

00:12:48.090 --> 00:12:52.030
because the energy of
the electromagnetic field

00:12:52.030 --> 00:12:55.660
is n plus 1/2 h bar omega.

00:12:55.660 --> 00:13:02.910
Whereas, this spontaneous
emission of eight is n plus 1.

00:13:02.910 --> 00:13:06.580
So you have half a photon
verse of extra energy.

00:13:06.580 --> 00:13:08.690
But this spontaneous
emission is sort

00:13:08.690 --> 00:13:13.240
of like the spontaneous
emission is the rate, which

00:13:13.240 --> 00:13:17.320
would be stimulated by an
extra energy of h bar omega.

00:13:17.320 --> 00:13:20.240
So in other words, you
would get the answer

00:13:20.240 --> 00:13:21.760
wrong by a factor of two.

00:13:24.650 --> 00:13:27.400
I think decoding deeper in the
electrodynamics description

00:13:27.400 --> 00:13:29.180
of spontaneous
emission you would

00:13:29.180 --> 00:13:32.560
identify two terms for
spontaneous emission.

00:13:32.560 --> 00:13:36.030
One is actually the stimulation
by the vacuum field.

00:13:36.030 --> 00:13:39.610
But there is another term
called radiation reaction.

00:13:39.610 --> 00:13:41.830
So there's, sort of, two terms.

00:13:41.830 --> 00:13:42.370
Trust me.

00:13:42.370 --> 00:13:44.590
If not, there are
hundreds of pages

00:13:44.590 --> 00:13:46.780
in [INAUDIBLE], which is
books written about it.

00:13:46.780 --> 00:13:50.910
And in the ground state, the two
terms destructively interfere.

00:13:50.910 --> 00:13:52.740
Therefore, you have no
spontaneous emission

00:13:52.740 --> 00:13:55.690
in the current state,
which is reassuring.

00:13:55.690 --> 00:13:58.730
But then in the excited
state the two terms

00:13:58.730 --> 00:14:00.580
constructively interfere.

00:14:00.580 --> 00:14:02.530
And therefore, you get
spontaneous emission,

00:14:02.530 --> 00:14:06.100
which is twice as much as
you would get if you just

00:14:06.100 --> 00:14:10.380
look at the stimulation
by the vacuum field.

00:14:10.380 --> 00:14:14.150
So the answer is not
quantitative but half of it,

00:14:14.150 --> 00:14:18.770
yes, can be regarded
as stimulated emission

00:14:18.770 --> 00:14:21.410
by the vacuum fluctuations
of the electromagnetic field.

00:14:26.861 --> 00:14:27.360
OK.

00:14:32.060 --> 00:14:35.920
We emphasized that
spontaneous emission

00:14:35.920 --> 00:14:37.930
is proportional to omega cube.

00:14:46.110 --> 00:14:53.720
The question is now what is the
dependence in one dimension?

00:14:53.720 --> 00:14:56.860
If everything the atom can
only emit in one dimension,

00:14:56.860 --> 00:15:01.090
everything is one dimensional,
put the atom into a waveguide.

00:15:01.090 --> 00:15:17.330
So your choices are omega cube,
omega square, or omega-- well,

00:15:17.330 --> 00:15:21.082
if you press D,
none of the above.

00:15:21.082 --> 00:15:23.750
But I can already tell you
it's one of those three.

00:15:34.950 --> 00:15:37.590
So everything the same.

00:15:37.590 --> 00:15:40.510
But we are in one dimension.

00:15:40.510 --> 00:15:43.804
The world seen by the atom and
by the electromagnetic waves

00:15:43.804 --> 00:15:44.595
is one dimensional.

00:15:52.910 --> 00:15:55.100
Yes, it's correct.

00:15:55.100 --> 00:15:59.730
As you remember, out of
the omega cube dependence.

00:15:59.730 --> 00:16:03.200
Omega square came from
the density of states.

00:16:03.200 --> 00:16:05.580
And what is omega square
in three dimension

00:16:05.580 --> 00:16:09.300
becomes omega in two
dimensions and constant density

00:16:09.300 --> 00:16:11.250
of state in one dimension.

00:16:11.250 --> 00:16:14.800
So therefore, in
one dimension, we

00:16:14.800 --> 00:16:18.875
are only left with
the omega dependence.

00:16:25.090 --> 00:16:28.530
OK, so there is one
factor of omega,

00:16:28.530 --> 00:16:32.460
which does not come from
the density of state.

00:16:32.460 --> 00:16:45.560
And the next question is where
does the other power of omega

00:16:45.560 --> 00:16:46.210
come from?

00:16:50.230 --> 00:16:52.500
As we discussed, it's not
the density of states.

00:16:55.440 --> 00:16:59.530
So we have three choices.

00:16:59.530 --> 00:17:04.430
One is it comes from the
atomic matrix element,

00:17:04.430 --> 00:17:09.550
it comes from the
dipole approximation,

00:17:09.550 --> 00:17:12.640
or it comes from
the quantization

00:17:12.640 --> 00:17:14.130
of the electromagnetic field.

00:17:47.790 --> 00:17:50.560
OK, the majority got it right.

00:17:50.560 --> 00:17:51.766
It's a field quantization.

00:17:55.830 --> 00:17:59.490
Sort of remember when you
write down the electric dipole

00:17:59.490 --> 00:18:02.830
Hamiltonian, in the
quantized version,

00:18:02.830 --> 00:18:05.870
there is a perfecter,
which is electric field

00:18:05.870 --> 00:18:08.430
of a single photon.

00:18:08.430 --> 00:18:13.860
So if you have a
single photon, it

00:18:13.860 --> 00:18:18.450
gives rise to an
electric field squared,

00:18:18.450 --> 00:18:20.262
which is proportionate
to h bar omega.

00:18:20.262 --> 00:18:22.220
And this is, sort of,
the normalization factor.

00:18:34.070 --> 00:18:34.890
Two more questions.

00:18:44.400 --> 00:18:47.910
We talked a lot about the
rotating wave approximation.

00:18:47.910 --> 00:18:52.710
And we also talked about
it for a spinning system

00:18:52.710 --> 00:18:54.560
driven by magnetic field.

00:18:54.560 --> 00:18:56.460
If you have a rotating
magnetic field,

00:18:56.460 --> 00:18:59.180
we do not need the
rotating wave approximation

00:18:59.180 --> 00:19:01.490
because if you drive a
spin system with a rotating

00:19:01.490 --> 00:19:06.820
magnetic field, we have
only the co-rotating term.

00:19:06.820 --> 00:19:11.680
The question I have now for you
is whether the same is correct

00:19:11.680 --> 00:19:14.520
or not for an
electronic transition.

00:19:14.520 --> 00:19:23.640
So therefore, the question
is for electronic transitions

00:19:23.640 --> 00:19:35.025
do we always get the
counter rotating term.

00:19:37.610 --> 00:19:40.890
And if you want to have
a simple Hamiltonian,

00:19:40.890 --> 00:19:43.640
then we do the rotating
wave approximation.

00:19:43.640 --> 00:19:47.680
So the question is is the
rotating wave approximation

00:19:47.680 --> 00:19:51.560
necessary because we always
get the counter rotating

00:19:51.560 --> 00:19:53.610
term for the
electronic transition,

00:19:53.610 --> 00:19:55.530
then the answer is yes.

00:19:55.530 --> 00:20:02.390
Or are there examples
where the system is exactly

00:20:02.390 --> 00:20:04.160
described by only one term?

00:20:04.160 --> 00:20:05.444
The core rotating term.

00:20:26.230 --> 00:20:28.987
I will come back to
that later in the class.

00:20:28.987 --> 00:20:30.445
But I thought it's
a good question.

00:20:35.410 --> 00:20:39.290
OK, let me give you the answer.

00:20:39.290 --> 00:20:41.680
I actually coincide with
everybody in the class

00:20:41.680 --> 00:20:49.420
here because I would tend to say
no because there are situations

00:20:49.420 --> 00:20:53.910
where the counter
rotating term can be zero

00:20:53.910 --> 00:21:00.620
due to angular momentum
selection rules.

00:21:04.050 --> 00:21:08.380
However, if you have an
electronic transition

00:21:08.380 --> 00:21:11.050
and you have a sigma plus
transition to one state,

00:21:11.050 --> 00:21:14.090
there's always a possibility
for sigma minus transition.

00:21:14.090 --> 00:21:16.370
So you usually get both.

00:21:16.370 --> 00:21:20.550
But if you apply an infinitely
strong magnetic field,

00:21:20.550 --> 00:21:23.060
then the m equals
minus 1 state can

00:21:23.060 --> 00:21:24.690
be moved out of the picture.

00:21:24.690 --> 00:21:27.530
You have only, let's say,
the m equals plus 1 state.

00:21:27.530 --> 00:21:31.500
And then selection holds mean
that the counter rotating

00:21:31.500 --> 00:21:36.690
term is vanishingly small.

00:21:36.690 --> 00:21:40.130
But it's an
artificial situation.

00:21:40.130 --> 00:21:44.630
So you can all claim
credit for your answer.

00:21:44.630 --> 00:21:52.140
Finally, the last question
is about the Lamb shift.

00:22:00.062 --> 00:22:04.720
We are now talking about
electronic transitions.

00:22:04.720 --> 00:22:14.960
And the question is
Lamb shift-- if it's

00:22:14.960 --> 00:22:16.660
