00:41:12.360 --> 00:41:15.565
So this was when we only
looked at the stimulated term

00:41:15.565 --> 00:41:18.990
when we only did
perturbation theory.

00:41:18.990 --> 00:41:26.040
And in that situation, we had
the electronic excitation.

00:41:26.040 --> 00:41:31.540
And then we had the
drive field, which

00:41:31.540 --> 00:41:35.940
was assumed to be purely
classical like a rotating

00:41:35.940 --> 00:41:40.390
magnetic field which drives
spin up spin down transitions

00:41:40.390 --> 00:41:42.250
magnetically.

00:41:42.250 --> 00:41:47.980
And we concluded that, yes,
if you use a laser field,

00:41:47.980 --> 00:41:51.520
it does exactly the same
to a two level atom what

00:41:51.520 --> 00:41:54.250
a magnetic field does
to spin up spin down.

00:41:54.250 --> 00:41:56.140
But now we are one step further.

00:41:56.140 --> 00:41:58.310
We've quantized the
electromagnetic field.

00:41:58.310 --> 00:42:00.100
And we have
spontaneous emission.

00:42:00.100 --> 00:42:02.960
And this is something, for
reasons I just mentioned,

00:42:02.960 --> 00:42:05.260
you will never find
in spin up spin down

00:42:05.260 --> 00:42:07.790
because it will take 1,000
years for spontaneous emission

00:42:07.790 --> 00:42:08.750
to happen.

00:42:08.750 --> 00:42:13.080
So now we want to actually
go beyond this semi classical

00:42:13.080 --> 00:42:15.500
picture, which is fully
analogous to the precession

00:42:15.500 --> 00:42:18.064
and rotation of the spin
in a magnetic field.

00:42:18.064 --> 00:42:19.730
And we want to add
spontaneous emission.

00:42:30.830 --> 00:42:35.360
So what we had here
is the Rabi frequency

00:42:35.360 --> 00:42:38.000
was a matrix element--
the dipole matrix

00:42:38.000 --> 00:42:42.790
element-- times a
classic electric field.

00:42:42.790 --> 00:42:47.760
And we want to replace that
now by the electric field

00:42:47.760 --> 00:42:49.550
at the position of the atom.

00:42:49.550 --> 00:42:52.500
But we want to use the
fully quantized version

00:42:52.500 --> 00:42:53.520
of the electric field.

00:42:56.929 --> 00:43:04.930
And it also becomes useful to
look at the sigma x operator,

00:43:04.930 --> 00:43:11.480
which actually has two matrix
elements of [INAUDIBLE], which

00:43:11.480 --> 00:43:15.830
connects ground excited
and excited ground state.

00:43:15.830 --> 00:43:21.980
And one of them is going from
the excited to the ground

00:43:21.980 --> 00:43:22.910
state.

00:43:22.910 --> 00:43:25.460
So this is, sort of,
lowering the energy

00:43:25.460 --> 00:43:27.700
to sigma minus operator.

00:43:27.700 --> 00:43:30.780
And the other one will
be a raising operator.

00:43:30.780 --> 00:43:33.510
It raises the
excitation of the atom.

00:43:33.510 --> 00:43:35.430
And we will refer
to it as sigma plus.

00:43:38.330 --> 00:43:45.370
So the electric
field is replaced

00:43:45.370 --> 00:43:49.567
by the operator obtained from
the fully quantized picture.

00:43:52.700 --> 00:43:59.240
Here we have the
prefactor, which

00:43:59.240 --> 00:44:03.400
is the electric field of a
single photon or half a photon,

00:44:03.400 --> 00:44:04.160
whatever.

00:44:04.160 --> 00:44:07.789
But it's factors of
2 r square over 2.

00:44:07.789 --> 00:44:08.830
We have the polarization.

00:44:08.830 --> 00:44:17.280
And now if you would
take the previous result

00:44:17.280 --> 00:44:20.210
and would look at it.

00:44:20.210 --> 00:44:22.430
Well we want to go to
the Schrodinger picture.

00:44:22.430 --> 00:44:24.760
And I mentioned that in
the Schrodinger picture

00:44:24.760 --> 00:44:27.010
the operators are
time independent.

00:44:27.010 --> 00:44:29.970
So we cancelled the e
to the i omega t term.

00:44:29.970 --> 00:44:33.490
If you would go to the
result we had last week

00:44:33.490 --> 00:44:37.320
