00:45:14.380 --> 00:45:17.790
So we're not looking e to
the i omega t or t equals 0.

00:45:17.790 --> 00:45:22.430
We wait a quarter period into e
to the i omega t just gives us

00:45:22.430 --> 00:45:26.800
factors of i, which conveniently
cancel the other factors of i.

00:45:26.800 --> 00:45:31.300
So what I'm doing is
just for convenience.

00:45:31.300 --> 00:45:40.296
And let me write down that this
is in the Schrodinger picture.

00:45:48.336 --> 00:45:48.835
OK.

00:45:53.620 --> 00:46:02.980
So we want to absorb all
constant by in one constant

00:46:02.980 --> 00:46:07.600
now, which is the single
photon Rabi frequency.

00:46:07.600 --> 00:46:12.730
We have the type or matrix
element of the atom.

00:46:12.730 --> 00:46:16.920
There's a dot product with
the polarization of the light.

00:46:16.920 --> 00:46:19.570
And then we have the
electric field amplitude

00:46:19.570 --> 00:46:20.770
of a single photon.

00:46:20.770 --> 00:46:25.170
h bar omega over 2 epsilon 0 v.

00:46:25.170 --> 00:46:29.210
So this is what appears
in the coupling.

00:46:29.210 --> 00:46:35.200
And we want to write it
s h bar omega 1 over 2.

00:46:35.200 --> 00:46:40.930
And this omega 1 is the
single photon Rabi frequency.

00:46:40.930 --> 00:46:44.730
And with that, we have
now a Hamiltonian,

00:46:44.730 --> 00:46:47.700
which is really a classic
Hamiltonian, written down

00:46:47.700 --> 00:46:49.430
in the standard form.

00:46:51.940 --> 00:46:59.820
It has the excitation energy
times the sigma z matrix.

00:46:59.820 --> 00:47:04.712
It has the single
photon Rabi frequency.

00:47:04.712 --> 00:47:13.150
The single photon Rabi
frequency appears.

00:47:13.150 --> 00:47:16.690
You know, this is the single
photon Rabi frequency.

00:47:16.690 --> 00:47:19.650
But then the operator
for the electric field,

00:47:19.650 --> 00:47:23.520
after getting rid off the i's,
is simply h plus h dagger.

00:47:29.460 --> 00:47:33.510
h plus h dagger.

00:47:33.510 --> 00:47:37.130
So this takes care
of the photon field.

00:47:37.130 --> 00:47:39.680
And the operator which
acts on the atoms

00:47:39.680 --> 00:47:43.920
are the raising and lowering
operator sigma plus and sigma

00:47:43.920 --> 00:47:45.390
minus.

00:47:45.390 --> 00:47:50.420
And finally, we have
the Hamiltonian,

00:47:50.420 --> 00:47:52.870
which describes the
photon field which

00:47:52.870 --> 00:48:01.170
is h bar omega times a dagger
a the photon number operator.

00:48:05.170 --> 00:48:06.330
Any questions?

00:48:06.330 --> 00:48:07.770
Yes?

00:48:07.770 --> 00:48:08.730
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]?

00:48:20.076 --> 00:48:21.450
